--------------------
objectives:
- how to use the PostgreSQL CLI to restore a full database from a backup.
- using a combination of the CLI and pgAdmin, make some changes to this database and perform a full backup.
- delete this database to practice a full restoration in the scenario of an accidental deletion with pgAdmin.

---------------------------
- for the fool restore in the Cloud IDE, enter the following command
  to create a backup of the restored_demo called restored_demo_backup.sql database:
pg_dump --username=postgres --host=localhost restored_demo > restored_demo_backup.sql